  <h1>Jägerschnitzel Recipe</h1>
<img src="https://github.com/student1840/Portfolio-Project-ITS335/blob/main/Raw%20Meat.jpg?raw=true" style="max-width: 100%; height: auto;" alt="Picture of Uncooked Meat">
<h2>Ingredients</h2>
<ul>
<li>4 thin sliced boneless pork chops</li>
<li>1-1/4 cups of all-purpose flour</li>
<li>2 large eggs</li>
<li>1 cup plain breadcrumbs</li>
<li>Clarified butter</li>
<li>1 eight-ounce can of mushrooms</li>
<li>2 cups beef stock/broth</li>
<li>1/4 tsp black pepper</li>
<li>Salt</li>
</ul>
</div>
<div class="section">
  <img src="https://github.com/student1840/Portfolio-Project-ITS335/blob/main/Flour%20and%20Egg.jpg?raw=true" style="max-width: 100%; height: auto;" alt="Picture of Eggs and Flour">
<h2>Directions</h2>
<ol>
<li>Place boneless pork chops between plastic wrap and use a meat tenderizer to pound until they are about a 1/4 inch thick.</li>
<li>Set up a breading station with three shallow dishes: one with flour, one with beaten eggs, and one with breadcrumbs.</li>
<li>Coat each pork chop with flour, then dip in egg, then press into breadcrumbs until evenly coated. Don't press too hard as you want a loose coating.</li>
<li>In a large skillet heat about a 1/4 inch of clarified butter over medium heat until simmering</li>
<li>Fry pork chops one or two at a time for about 2-3 minutes per side or until golden brown and crispy</li>
<li>Transfer to paper towels to drain, and keep warm in an oven set to low if necessary.</li>
<li>In a separate pan, melt 2 tablespoons of butter</li>
<li>Add flour and stir continuously for 1-1/2 minutes so the roux doesn't burn.</li>
<li>Slowly pour in the beef stock while stirring</li>
<li>Cook for 3 to 4 minutes, or until it thickens to a thin-syrup consistency. <li>Continue to stir gravy to avoid burning.</li>
<li>Drain mushrooms and add them to the gravy mixture. Continue to cook for another 2 minutes while stirring.</li>
</ol>
  <img src="https://github.com/student1840/Portfolio-Project-ITS335/blob/main/Jager%20Schnitzel%20Picture.jpg?raw=true" style="max-width: 100%; height: auto;" alt="Picture of Eggs and Flour">
